#. <section class="sutta" id="sn11.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.7:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. The First Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn11.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Nadubbhiyasutta"
msgstr "7. Not Betray"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.485"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.7:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn11.7:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, sakkassa devānamindassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa "
"evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"“Once upon a time, mendicants, as Sakka, lord of gods, was in private "
"retreat this thought came to his mind:"

# BB’s “Transgress against” seems vague and weak, especially when referring to someone you’re in constant war against. The root is the same as mittadduno.
msgctxt "sn11.7:1.3"
msgid "‘yopi me assa supaccatthiko tassapāhaṃ na dubbheyyan’ti."
msgstr "‘I should never betray even a sworn enemy.’"

msgctxt "sn11.7:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vepacitti asurindo sakkassa devānamindassa cetasā "
"cetoparivitakkamaññāya yena sakko devānamindo tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""
"And then Vepacitti, lord of demons, knowing what Sakka was thinking, "
"approached him."

msgctxt "sn11.7:1.5"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo vepacittiṃ asurindaṃ dūratova "
"āgacchantaṃ."
msgstr "Sakka saw Vepacitti coming off in the distance,"

msgctxt "sn11.7:1.6"
msgid "Disvāna vepacittiṃ asurindaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn11.7:1.7"
msgid "‘tiṭṭha, vepacitti, gahitosī’ti."
msgstr "‘Stop, Vepacitti, you’re caught!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: tadeva tvaṃ mā pajahāsī’ti → tadeva tvaṃ mārisa pahāsīti (bj) | tadeva tvaṃ mārisa jahāsīti (s1-3, km) | tad eva tvam mā pahāsīti (pts1)
msgctxt "sn11.7:2.1"
msgid "‘Yadeva te, mārisa, pubbe cittaṃ, tadeva tvaṃ mā pajahāsī’ti."
msgstr "‘Dear sir, don’t give up the idea you just had!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: adubbhāyā’ti → adrubbhāya (mr)
msgctxt "sn11.7:3.1"
msgid "‘Sapassu ca me, vepacitti, adubbhāyā’ti."
msgstr "‘Swear, Vepacitti, that you won’t betray me.’"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.7:4.1"
msgid "‘Yaṃ musā bhaṇato pāpaṃ,"
msgstr "‘Whatever bad things happen to a liar,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.7:4.2"
msgid "Yaṃ pāpaṃ ariyūpavādino;"
msgstr "or to someone who slanders the noble ones,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.7:4.3"
msgid "Mittadduno ca yaṃ pāpaṃ,"
msgstr "or to someone who betrays a friend,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.7:4.4"
msgid "Yaṃ pāpaṃ akataññuno;"
msgstr "or to someone who’s ungrateful:"

#. <br>
#. VAR: phusatu → phusati (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn11.7:4.5"
msgid "Tameva pāpaṃ phusatu,"
msgstr "the same bad things impact"

# Vepacitti is reminding Sakka of their family connection.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.7:4.6"
msgid "Yo te dubbhe sujampatī’”ti."
msgstr "anyone who betrays you, Sujā’s husband.’”"
